    <div>
      <h3>How to recognize quality crystal?</h3>
      <h2>1. THICKNESS</h2>
      <p>It takes a great deal of experience for a glass blower to blow crystal very thin and consistent throughout. Check the thickness of the glass.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>How to recognize quality crystal?</h3>
      <h2>3. SOFT EDGES</h2>
      <p>Examine the cuts on the crystal item. Normal glass has often sharp cuts, while crystal has smooth, rounded cuts.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>How to recognize quality crystal?</h3>
      <h2>2. WEIGHT</h2>
      <p>High quality crystal contains at least 24% lead oxide (PbO), which is a fairly heavy and relatively expensive ingredient. Cheap crystal uses less than 24% and will therefor feel lighter than high quality crystal. You can weigh 2 glasses of roughly the same size to see which one is heaviest. This might be an indication of quality.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>How to recognize quality crystal?</h3>
      <h2>4. CRYSTAL CLEAR</h2>
      <p>Hold the item up to the light. Glass typically has a yellow or green tint, while crystal is completely clear. Crystal also produces more of a colourful prism effect than glass.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>How to recognize quality crystal?</h3>
      <h2>6. CERTIFICATION</h2>
      <p>Only high quality crystal of at least 24% PbO can have, by European law, a round golden sticker on it. Be wary of square or any other shape of stickers. All BrenndeL's crystal items are certified 24% PbO and you will always find our round gold sticker on the foot of the glass.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>How to recognize quality crystal?</h3>
      <h2>5. SOUND</h2>
      <p>Tap the item and take note of the sound it makes. Glass usually has more of a dull thud, and crystal has more of a high-pitched chime.</p>
